---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE, CONTACT } from '../../data/site';

const schemas = [
  {
    '@context': 'https://schema.org',
    '@type': 'Article',
    headline: 'Security Assessment: Mobile Money Platform',
    description:
      'Anonymised case study of a security assessment for a mobile money platform in East Africa. USSD session fixation, hardcoded encryption keys, and negative transaction vulnerabilities.',
    author: {
      '@type': 'Organization',
      name: 'imizicyber',
      url: SITE.url,
    },
    publisher: {
      '@type': 'Organization',
      name: 'imizicyber',
      url: SITE.url,
    },
  },
  {
    '@context': 'https://schema.org',
    '@type': 'BreadcrumbList',
    itemListElement: [
      { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 1, name: 'Home', item: `${SITE.url}/` },
      {
        '@type': 'ListItem',
        position: 2,
        name: 'Case Studies',
        item: `${SITE.url}/case-studies/`,
      },
      {
        '@type': 'ListItem',
        position: 3,
        name: 'Mobile Money Platform',
        item: `${SITE.url}/case-studies/mobile-money-security-assessment/`,
      },
    ],
  },
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Case Study: Security Assessment — Mobile Money Platform | imizicyber"
  description="Anonymised case study of a security assessment for a mobile money platform in East Africa. USSD session fixation, hardcoded encryption keys, and transaction fraud vulnerabilities."
  canonicalUrl={`${SITE.url}/case-studies/mobile-money-security-assessment/`}
  schemas={schemas}
  whatsappMessage="Hi imizicyber, I saw your mobile money case study and would like to discuss security testing"
  navVariant="inner"
  footerVariant="inner"
>
  <div class="w">
    <div class="article-header">
      <div class="breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a><span class="sep">/</span><a href="/case-studies/">Case Studies</a><span
          class="sep">/</span
        ><span>Mobile Money Platform</span>
      </div>
      <div class="article-meta">
        <span class="label">CASE STUDY</span>
        <span class="sep">&middot;</span>
        <span class="detail">SECURITY ASSESSMENT</span>
      </div>
      <h1>Security Assessment: Mobile Money Platform</h1>
      <p class="article-intro">
        A mobile money platform processing over 2 million daily transactions needed an independent
        security assessment before PCI DSS certification. Here is what we found.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="w article-body">
    <h2>Client description</h2>
    <p>
      A mobile network operator's fintech subsidiary providing mobile money services across three
      East African countries. The platform processed over 2 million transactions daily, serving both
      individual consumers and merchant payments. The company was preparing for a PCI DSS
      certification audit and needed an independent security assessment.
    </p>

    <h2>Engagement type</h2>
    <p>
      Comprehensive security assessment including mobile application testing (Android and iOS), USSD
      interface testing, API security review, and infrastructure assessment. The engagement ran for
      4 weeks, covering the full transaction lifecycle from customer registration through payment
      processing.
    </p>

    <h2>Key findings</h2>
    <ol class="findings-list">
      <li>
        <span class="severity severity-critical">CRITICAL</span> USSD session fixation vulnerability allowed
        an attacker on the same mobile network to hijack active USSD sessions and authorize transactions
        on behalf of other users.
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="severity severity-critical">CRITICAL</span> The mobile app stored the user's PIN
        in encrypted SharedPreferences, but the encryption key was hardcoded in the APK. Reverse engineering
        the app exposed the PIN of any user whose device was physically accessed.
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="severity severity-high">HIGH</span> The merchant payment API accepted negative transaction
        amounts, allowing a crafted request to reverse funds from merchant accounts to the attacker's
        wallet.
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="severity severity-high">HIGH</span> Certificate pinning was implemented in the Android
        app but not enforced on the iOS version, enabling man-in-the-middle interception of API traffic
        on iOS devices.
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="severity severity-medium">MEDIUM</span> Agent registration API did not validate the
        national ID format, allowing registration with fabricated identities.
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="severity severity-low">LOW</span> Transaction notification SMS included full account
        numbers rather than masked versions, creating information disclosure risk on shared or stolen
        devices.
      </li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Business impact</h2>
    <p>
      The USSD session fixation could have enabled unauthorized fund transfers affecting any of the
      platform's 1.2 million active users. The hardcoded encryption key in the mobile app meant
      every customer's PIN was effectively stored in cleartext from a determined attacker's
      perspective. The negative transaction vulnerability could have been exploited for systematic
      fraud against merchants. These findings would have been blockers for PCI DSS certification.
    </p>

    <h2>Recommendations</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Implement server-side USSD session binding using device IMSI and timestamp validation</li>
      <li>
        Move PIN storage to platform-provided secure enclaves (Android Keystore / iOS Keychain) with
        biometric binding
      </li>
      <li>Add server-side transaction amount validation with strict positive-value enforcement</li>
      <li>Enforce certificate pinning on all mobile platforms</li>
      <li>Implement national ID format and checksum validation on registration endpoints</li>
      <li>Mask account numbers in all customer-facing notifications</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Outcome</h2>
    <p>
      The client prioritised the two critical findings for immediate remediation. All high and
      medium findings were addressed within 60 days. The security assessment report was submitted as
      evidence for their PCI DSS certification audit, which they passed on the subsequent attempt.
      The client engaged Imizi Cyber for ongoing quarterly assessments.
    </p>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <div class="cta-box">
      <h2>Need a security assessment for your platform?</h2>
      <p>
        We assess mobile money platforms, fintech apps, and payment systems across East Africa. Tell
        us what you need secured.
      </p>
      <div class="cta-btns">
        <button data-cal-link={CONTACT.calLink} class="btn btn-fill btn-cal">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 20 20" aria-hidden="true"
            ><path
              d="M6 2a1 1 0 00-1 1v1H4a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2h12a2 2 0 002-2V6a2 2 0 00-2-2h-1V3a1 1 0 10-2 0v1H7V3a1 1 0 00-1-1zm0 5a1 1 0 011 1v1h1a1 1 0 110 2H7v1a1 1 0 11-2 0v-1H4a1 1 0 110-2h1V8a1 1 0 011-1z"
            ></path></svg
          >
          Book a Free Call
        </button>
        <a
          href={`https://wa.me/250793146617?text=${encodeURIComponent('Hi imizicyber, I saw your mobile money case study and would like to discuss security testing')}`}
          class="btn btn-wa"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            ><path
              d="M17.472 14.382c-.297-.149-1.758-.867-2.03-.967-.273-.099-.471-.148-.67.15-.197.297-.767.966-.94 1.164-.173.199-.347.223-.644.075-.297-.15-1.255-.463-2.39-1.475-.883-.788-1.48-1.761-1.653-2.059-.173-.297-.018-.458.13-.606.134-.133.298-.347.446-.52.149-.174.198-.298.298-.497.099-.198.05-.371-.025-.52-.075-.149-.669-1.612-.916-2.207-.242-.579-.487-.5-.669-.51-.173-.008-.371-.01-.57-.01-.198 0-.52.074-.792.372-.272.297-1.04 1.016-1.04 2.479 0 1.462 1.065 2.875 1.213 3.074.149.198 2.096 3.2 5.077 4.487.709.306 1.262.489 1.694.625.712.227 1.36.195 1.871.118.571-.085 1.758-.719 2.006-1.413.248-.694.248-1.289.173-1.413-.074-.124-.272-.198-.57-.347z"
            ></path><path
              d="M12 0C5.373 0 0 5.373 0 12c0 2.625.846 5.059 2.284 7.034L.789 23.492a.5.5 0 00.611.611l4.458-1.495A11.952 11.952 0 0012 24c6.627 0 12-5.373 12-12S18.627 0 12 0zm0 21.75c-2.16 0-4.16-.696-5.788-1.876l-.404-.3-2.645.886.886-2.645-.3-.404A9.724 9.724 0 012.25 12C2.25 6.615 6.615 2.25 12 2.25S21.75 6.615 21.75 12 17.385 21.75 12 21.75z"
            ></path></svg
          >
          WhatsApp us
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* Blog-style narrow container */
  .w {
    max-width: 680px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 24px;
  }

  /* HEADER */
  .breadcrumb {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.64rem;
    color: var(--txt3);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 6px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .breadcrumb a {
    color: var(--txt3);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }
  .breadcrumb a:hover {
    color: var(--acc);
  }
  .breadcrumb .sep {
    color: var(--dim);
  }
  .article-header {
    padding: 100px 0 36px;
  }
  .article-meta {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.64rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    margin-bottom: 18px;
  }
  .article-meta .label {
    color: var(--acc);
  }
  .article-meta .sep {
    color: var(--txt3);
    margin: 0 6px;
  }
  .article-meta .detail {
    color: #f59e0b;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: clamp(1.7rem, 4vw, 2.3rem);
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: -1px;
    line-height: 1.12;
    color: var(--white);
    margin-bottom: 14px;
  }
  .article-intro {
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    color: var(--txt2);
    line-height: 1.7;
    max-width: 560px;
  }

  /* BODY CONTENT */
  .article-body h2 {
    font-size: clamp(1.15rem, 2vw, 1.4rem);
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: -0.5px;
    color: var(--white);
    margin-top: 40px;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
    line-height: 1.2;
  }
  .article-body p {
    margin-bottom: 14px;
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    color: var(--txt);
    line-height: 1.75;
  }
  .article-body a {
    color: var(--acc);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }
  .article-body a:hover {
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .article-body a.btn {
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .article-body ul {
    list-style: none;
    margin-bottom: 18px;
    padding: 0;
  }
  .article-body li {
    padding: 4px 0 4px 18px;
    position: relative;
    font-size: 0.84rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--txt);
  }
  .article-body li::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 11px;
    width: 5px;
    height: 5px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--acc);
  }
  .article-body strong {
    color: var(--white);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  /* FINDINGS LIST */
  .findings-list {
    list-style: none;
    counter-reset: finding;
    margin-bottom: 18px;
    padding: 0;
  }
  .findings-list li {
    counter-increment: finding;
    padding: 10px 0 10px 0;
    font-size: 0.84rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--txt);
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.04);
  }
  .findings-list li:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  /* SEVERITY TAGS */
  .severity {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.62rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    padding: 2px 8px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    margin-right: 8px;
    vertical-align: middle;
  }
  .severity-critical {
    background: rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.15);
    color: #ef4444;
    border: 1px solid rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.3);
  }
  .severity-high {
    background: rgba(249, 115, 22, 0.15);
    color: #f97316;
    border: 1px solid rgba(249, 115, 22, 0.3);
  }
  .severity-medium {
    background: rgba(234, 179, 8, 0.15);
    color: #eab308;
    border: 1px solid rgba(234, 179, 8, 0.3);
  }
  .severity-low {
    background: rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.15);
    color: #60a5fa;
    border: 1px solid rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.3);
  }

  /* CTA BOX */
  .cta-box {
    background: var(--bg3);
    border: 1px solid rgba(52, 211, 153, 0.15);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 36px;
    text-align: center;
    margin: 40px 0 20px;
  }
  .cta-box h2 {
    margin-top: 0;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
  }
  .cta-box p {
    color: var(--txt2);
    font-size: 0.84rem;
    margin-bottom: 18px;
  }
  .cta-btns {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 8px;
  }
  .btn {
    padding: 10px 22px;
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: all 0.2s;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
  }
  .btn-fill,
  .article-body .btn-fill {
    background: var(--accdark);
    color: #fff;
  }
  .btn-fill:hover {
    background: var(--acc2);
    box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(52, 211, 153, 0.15);
  }
  .btn-wa,
  .article-body .btn-wa {
    background: #1b7a42;
    color: #fff;
  }
  .btn-wa:hover {
    background: #166e3a;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(37, 211, 102, 0.2);
  }
  .btn-wa svg {
    width: 18px;
    height: 18px;
    fill: #fff;
  }

  /* LIGHT THEME */
  [data-theme='light'] .cta-box {
    border-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
  }
  [data-theme='light'] .btn-fill {
    color: #fff;
  }
  [data-theme='light'] .btn-wa {
    color: #fff;
  }
  [data-theme='light'] .findings-list li {
    border-bottom-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
  }

  /* RESPONSIVE - MOBILE */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .cta-box {
      padding: 24px;
    }
    .cta-btns {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
    }
    .article-header {
      padding: 76px 0 24px;
    }
  }

  /* RESPONSIVE - SMALL PHONE */
  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .w {
      padding: 0 16px;
    }
    .article-body h2 {
      margin-top: 28px;
    }
    .cta-box {
      padding: 20px;
    }
  }
</style>
